neo
------------------------------------------
neo recreates the digital rain effect from 'The Matrix'. Streams of random
characters will endlessly scroll down your terminal screen.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libncursesw10-6.5+20240427-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libncurses-devel-6.5+20240427-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/st3w/neo

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/st3w/neo/archive/refs/tags/v0.6.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack neo-0.6.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./neo-0.6.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/neo-0.6.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/neo-0.6.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(neo)
  /usr/bin/neo.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/neo.README
  /usr/share/doc/neo/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/neo/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man6/neo.6.gz

